                FLIR Systems - FLIR Infrared Cameras, FLIR Night Vision, FLIR Thermal Imaging Monoculars & More — 85 products / 121 models
 — Page 1























FLIR began by making thermal imagers that mounted on vehicles to help conduct energy audits in the late 70s. These audits helped homeowners find spots where hot or cold air was escaping. From their original focus of measuring tiny temperature changes from a distance, FLIR has expanded into markets where seeing in adverse conditions is vital. When there are contaminants in the air, the image from normal night vision devices can be obscured, but thermal imaging units pierce the fog to find heat signatures. Because of their amazing versatility and consistent performance, FLIR thermal imagers are a popular choice among firefighters, police officers and soldiers who have to rely on thermal vision units in life threatening situations. To narrow your search for just the right equipment from FLIR, use the handy category and product line filters below on the left. Read through reviews of FLIR products written by people like you. Remember, a FLIR warranty ensures your satisfaction with your purchase. For more help choosing durable, reliable FLIR products, check our informative blogs
and our article about the differences between thermal imaging and night vision.
Optics Planet proudly supplies needed equipment to military and law enforcement personnel. We offer Free Shipping on all orders over $49 as well as FREE Shipping to APOs and FPOs. Please refer to our APO/FPO Shipping and Export Restrictions for more information on export to APO/FPO addresses. Make OpticsPlanet.com your trusted procurement source for FLIR and all other military gear!







