The Ultimate Father's Day Gift
         Monday, June 12, 2017 
            





facebook





linkedin





twitter





print





 According to some accounts of Greek mythology, Zeus – the king of the gods – fathered a total of 92 children, making for some epic Father’s Days, no doubt, around the confines of Mount Olympus.While it’s unlikely that your own father enjoys a progeny as prodigious as that of Zeus, you can still make him feel like an immortal on Father’s Day, while reclaiming your rightful, favored status. How? By giving him the power of Zeus: the gift of unrivaled vision in any conditions, from full sunlight to total darkness.For the shooting or tactical-oriented dad, the Armasight by FLIR Zeus Pro Thermal Weapon Sight represents the ultimate expression of appreciation; it’s FLIR’s most versatile and sophisticated targeting product available for the consumer market. This isn’t night vision; Armasight by FLIR Zeus Pro is built with industry-leading FLIR thermal-imaging technology. When mounted to Dad’s gun or used as a handheld spotting scope, Zeus Pro detects minute differences in the temperatures of both live and inert objects and amplifies these differences to project amazingly clear images onto the unit’s screen. Utilizing FLIR’s field-proven Tau® 2 thermal camera core, the Zeus Pro is available in 336x256 or 640x512 pixel formats with professional-grade 50mm or 100mm Germanium (Ge) objective lenses. The result is a wide variety of optical magnifications and the ability to detect an average-sized person up to 1,000 yards away. Eight distinct models optimized for both medium- and long-range performance are available.Dad will definitely appreciate the Armasight by FLIR Zeus Pro Thermal Weapon Sight’s simple and intuitive controls, functions and features. Zeus Pro models mount and dismount quickly and easily via a MIL-STD-1913 rail, and feature ballistic reticles, an electronic compass and an inclinometer for finer range estimation and target orientation. An included multi-pin connector provides video-out/video-in capability, external power supply and support of accessories like an optional DVR or modular range finder. Operation and functions are also supported by an included wireless remote.Think Dad already has everything? Think again. Say thanks this Father’s Day by presenting him with the unrivaled vision of Zeus. We can’t predict his reaction, but one thing’s for certain: even if he does have 92 kids, you just became his favorite again.


