How FLIR Optical Gas Imaging Cameras Work
         Thursday, June 15, 2017 
            





facebook





linkedin





twitter





print





We know thermal cameras can see heat, but how are FLIR Optical Gas Imaging Cameras able to see gas? In visible light, gas is completely transmissive - light goes right through the molecules. However, many gases have infrared absorption characteristics that can be targeted with specially designed thermal imaging cameras. Watch this great video on how Optical Gas Imaging Cameras work:





 
Gain a greater understanding of optical gas imaging technology, and how you can use it to find and repair gas leaks quickly by downloading our free professional guide.
 


