FLIR Teams Up with AngelHack in 10th Global Hackathon Series
         Tuesday, June 13, 2017 
            





facebook





linkedin





twitter





print






This past weekend, FLIR brought the Bring the Heat Hacker & Maker Challenge back to the Big Apple by teaming up once again with our friends from AngelHack for their 10th Global Hackathon Series: Commit to Your Code. 
We are excited to welcome four new teams as part of our FLIR ONE developer community—BeerPong.com, for their application to test intoxication levels; Heat Check, a human detection app; RescuER, a search and rescue aid app for first responders; as well as our ultimate grand prize winners, Sunscreen Checkr, for their application to let you know where you missed a spot when applying sunscreen. Our winners, Sunscreen Checkr, will be traveling to visit FLIR Santa Barbara to pitch their app ideas to the FLIR team!  Thanks again to everyone who made this event possible, and a very special thanks to all participants.   






 
To learn more about the FLIR ONE Developer Program head to developer.flir.com.


